Instructions
===========

1. Install uv 
    - https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/installation/

2. Sync dependencies (GPU Setup)
    -Nvidia (Windows/Linux): Need [CUDA Toolkit 12.1+](https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-12-1-0-download-archive). `pyproject.toml` defaults to cu121. Just run `uv sync`.
    - Mac (Silicon): No extra drivers needed. Edit `pyproject.toml`: remove `[[tool.uv.index]]` block and `+cu121` suffix from torch/torchvision. Run `uv sync`.
    - AMD (Linux): Need [ROCm drivers](https://rocm.docs.amd.com/en/latest/deploy/linux/index.html). Change index URL in `pyproject.toml` to `https://download.pytorch.org/whl/rocm6.0`. Run `uv sync`.

3. Download the data
    - uv run main.py download --dataset cbsd68

=====

uv run main.py train \
  --sigma 25 \
  --stages 5 \
  --epochs 30 \
  --filters 24 \
  --filter-size 7 \
  --loss mse \
  --phi soft_threshold \
  --gamma 0.5 \
  --train-on cbsd68 \
  --visualize-every 5


uv run main.py evaluate checkpoints/sigma25_final.pt \
  --test-on cbsd68 \
  --show-diffusion \
  --save-images
